Sins | 2005 | Critically Acclaimed | DVDRip | LKRG | Phantom


Sins is a controversial 2005 Bollywood film directed and produced by Joy Augustine. The film involves a Catholic priest who is romantically involved with a young woman. The film was protested against by those that felt it was a negative portrayal of Catholicism and indecent. It received an A (adults only rating) due to themes and revealing scenes.

The film was based on news story Pande read in 1988 about a Kerala priest sentenced to death on sexual harassment and murder charges.

